APPIUM FRAMEWORK DEVELOPMENT PLAN 

  i. Create Maven project for framework structire generation //build management tool
  ii. Build Appium tests in project 
  iii. Develop a plan to define global properties for Appium Desired capabilities
  iv. Make the tests TestNG compatible to utilize the features of TestNG framework
  v. Make Page Object Model design pattern for the tests so that objects should not stay in TestCases
  vi. Develop Appium custom utilities to avoid duplicate code
  vii. Build utilities to start & stop Appium server programmatically
  viii. Give a knowledge to framework to invoke Emulator on fly if Virual device option is selected
  ix. Build TestNG Listeners to capture screenshots on Test failures
  x. Generate Excellent client-side Reports on Test Results with Graphs
  xi. Implement Data Driven & Parameterization mechanism to drive Test Data externally into Tests
  xii. Integrate Framework repo into Jenkins CI tool
  xiii. Parametrize the Jenkins build so that user have option to select Mobile device 
        which needed to run tests for that specific build
  xiv. Push your framework changes into GIT repository . 
        
        